We begin with the line given by the first equation, $y=\green{-7}x+\pink{3}
$. We know the $y$-intercept is $(0,\pink{3})$, so this is one of our points. Since the slope of the line is $\green{-7}$, we know that another point on the line is $(1,\pink{3}\green{-7})$, which is the point $(1,-4)$.

In a similar manner, we will find that the line given by the second equation passes through $(0,-3)$ and $(1,-4)$.

